          • [ - ] Turan - member since 22-Nov-13

            Part 2 Nacho, honestly doesnt seem that good. I mean dont get me wrong, to be able to be part of Real Madrid you need to be at least decent, which he is, but he doesnt have that spark that for example Varane has when playing. He isnt fast, nor is he dominant in the air and you cant really call him a tactical genius. His tackling isnt that good either. Overall he is a decent, solid defender but thats it and honestly i dont see him being part of the starting 11. On the other hand, since you need players that accept being benched and still work hard for when the team needs them due to first 11 members being suspended/injured, now thats a role for Nacho. Being a player from the castilla he surely has the will power to wait for chances and be patient. This role suits him and thats why in my opinion he is with the squad this year, being 4th in line after Ramos,Varane and Pepe, to cover injuries/suspensions. Llorente is a player who we have to see first before we can make any assestments.

          • [ - ] Turan - member since 22-Nov-13

            Part 1 Regarding the talk thats been going on about Llorente, Nacho, Varane and Pepe: Varane is a world class defender and the only problem is that he has had far too many injuries and those that a player carries all of his career (knee). So the case of Varane is difficult because if he is fit he is better then most defenders in Europe but he is prone to injuries. Pepe has steadily declined over the past few seasons. He has lost pace and the kind of quick thinking that is a must when playing at central defence. On the other hand he has gained experience and if he performs well at the moment that is because he is playing more with his brain now (as funny as it might sound for a player prone to red cards due to bad temper). He has been at the team quite some time now and since center backs similar to keepers can play more years than players of other positions, he is likely to remain till at least the 2014-2015 season ends even if he isnt a starter and he is used as part of rotation.
